As reformed Christians, the 5 Solas encompass the core theological convictions of reformed Christianity that distinguish it from other doctrines

Sola is a latin word that means alone or only


--> Scripture alone. The bible is the sole source of faith and holds authority over church tradition

--> Faith alone. Salvation is received by faith, apart from any human works

--> Grace alone. Salvation is a free gift from God, entirely offered by His grace rather than human effort

--> Christ alone. Jesus Christ is the only mediator between God and man, and salvation is found through only his work on the cross

--> Glory to God alone. All glory is due to God alone, salvation is accomplished solely through His will and action



