Salt and Light

- Before the days of refrigeration, salt was used as a preservative by rubbing it into meat. The salt preserved the meat from degradation and rot
- Similarly, Christians as the salt of the earth preserve Gods presence in order to prevent degradation into sin

- As salt preserves meat from rotting, believers in Jesus, distributed around the world, help to preserve humanity from falling into godlessness, immorality, chaos, and the resulting judgment.
- Salt permanently changes the flavor of food, just as the influence of godly people can change a culture.

- If salt is diluted or contaminated, it loses it's value and becomes worthless and to be disposed of

Jesus compares disciples to salt as a preservative and then compares them to light 

The light of Christ is meant to shine brightly so those in darkness can see it. It is meant to be discovered

salt has a positive, preserving influence on food and followers of Christ have a positive, preserving influence on humanity and culture

Light: visibility, truth and guidance




